Explanation:

The solution uses a helper function to count the number of characters in the word that are present in the given string of characters. The main function iterates over each word and calls the helper function to count the characters. The containsChar function checks if a character is present in the given string of characters. The overall efficiency is high because the main function iterates over the words once and the helper function is called once for each word. The time complexity is O(n) where n is the number of words, and the space complexity is O(n) as well, where n is the number of words. The energy implications are low because the solution only requires a constant amount of energy to run.

